# Changelog

## [0.2.2] - 2026-04-03
### Fix: lazy LLM instantiation — no API key required at import time
- Replaced module-level `ChatOpenAI(...)` calls in `llm_model.py` with lazy singleton factory functions `get_llm_low()` and `get_llm_high()`; instances are created only on first use
- Converted `default_llm`, `llm_analyst`, `llm_outline`, `llm_text`, `llm_check_title`, and `llm_title_abstract` from module-level instance aliases to thin wrapper functions
- Updated `LLMNodes/LLMNode.py`: imports `get_llm_low` and calls it in `get_llm()` instead of referencing the former module-level `default_llm`
- Updated `CheckTitleRelevance.py`: imports `get_llm_low` and calls it at chain construction time instead of binding the former module-level `llm_low`
- `import black_langcube` now succeeds without `OPENAI_API_KEY` being set

## [0.2.1] - 2026-03-18
### Minor fixes and improvements
- Updated `pyproject.toml` version to `0.2.1`

## [0.2.0] - 2026-03-17
### Full async upgrade
- Added `llm_modules/robust_invoke_async.py` — async version of `robust_invoke` using `chain.ainvoke` and `asyncio.sleep`
- Upgraded `LLMNode.run_chain()` and `LLMNode.execute()` to `async def`
- Upgraded `translator_en_subgraph.py` and `translator_usr_subgraph.py` `execute()` to `async def`
- Upgraded `graph_base.py`: `graph_streaming()` uses `graph.astream()`, `write_events_to_file()` uses `aiofiles`, `get_language()`, `get_message()`, `run_base()`, and `run()` all `async def`; added `session_id` parameter to `__init__`
- Upgraded all three subgrafs (`translator_en`, `translator_usr`, `message_translator`) `run()` to `async def`
- Upgraded all message functions (`message_graph1–5`, `compose_message`, `message_end_process`, subgraph message functions) to `async def`
- Added `get_result_from_graph_outputs_async` and `get_simple_result_from_graph_outputs_async` wrappers (via `asyncio.to_thread`) to `get_result_from_graph_outputs.py`
- Upgraded `submodules.py` `end_process()` to `async def`
- Upgraded `graf1.py`–`graf5.py` mock implementations: `time.sleep` → `asyncio.sleep`, sync file I/O → `aiofiles`, `run()` → `async def`
- Upgraded `process.py`: all public and private functions (`run_workflow_by_id`, `_run_graph1–5`, `run_complete_pipeline`, `cleanup_session`) → `async def`
- Upgraded all examples (`basic_workflow.py`, `library_usage.py`, `custom_llm_node.py`, `translation_workflow.py`) to use `async def` and `asyncio.run()`
- Added `aiofiles` to package dependencies in `pyproject.toml`

## [0.1.2] - 2026-03-16
### LangChain compatibility update
- Updated `robust_invoke` imports to support newer LangChain versions
- Replaced deprecated `langchain.schema.OutputParserException` with `langchain_core.exceptions.OutputParserException`
- Replaced `pydantic.v1.ValidationError` import with `pydantic.ValidationError`

## [0.1.1] - 2025-09-09
### Project link fixes
- Fixed project links in the documentation
- Updated README with correct URLs

## [0.1.0] - 2025-09-08
### Initial public release
- First version of the library

## [0.0.3] - 2025-07-24
### Proper library structure
- Restructured the library layout for better organization
- Improved module imports and exports

## [0.0.2] - 2025-07-23
### Examples tuned and file cleanup
- Updated examples to better reflect usage
- Removed unused files and directories

## [0.0.1] - 2025-06-30
### Uploaded
- First version of extension